STEP 1: Install Node.js

Download:

Node.js Official Website

Install LTS version.

Check:

node -v
npm -v
STEP 2: Install Git

Download:

Git Official Website

Check:

git --version
STEP 3: Clone Your GitHub Repository

Open terminal:

git clone https://github.com/Dnyaneshsasale/smart-study-scheduler.git
STEP 4: Open Project Folder
cd smart-study-scheduler
STEP 5: Install Required Packages

VERY IMPORTANT

Run:

npm install

This installs:

express
mongoose
ejs
body-parser
STEP 6: Start Project

Run:

node app.js
STEP 7: Open Browser

Open:

http://localhost:3000

Your project runs.
